Absolutely. I'll answer as if I were mentoring a junior developer who wants to become an excellent Java engineer over the next few years.

The first thing I'd tell you is this:

> **Don't try to learn Java, DSA, Spring Boot, Microservices, Docker, Kubernetes, System Design, and AI all at once.** Most beginners fail because they learn everything simultaneously and master nothing.

When I started (imagining my career as a senior engineer), I also wouldn't have known much initially. The difference between someone who becomes an excellent engineer and someone who struggles isn't intelligence—it's **consistency and deliberate practice**.

