# My DSA Rule

Never copy code immediately.

Instead

Take one problem.

Think for 30 minutes.

Even if you fail

That thinking develops problem-solving skills.

After that

Watch one solution.

Close it.

Write it again from memory.

Next day

Solve it again.

One week later

Solve it again.

This spaced repetition helps the techniques stick.

